#-*-org-*-

* At each keypress, add the text to a display area
Right now it's "line oriented": nothing changes in the display area
until you click the "Done" button on the keyboard.

http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/text/creating-input-method.html
might be where to look if I need to write my own "Input Method
Editor", given that the built-in keyboard seems not to deliver
individual keypresses.

http://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/inputmethod/InputConnection.html
might also be useful; it has a "sendKeyEvent" method.

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4462045/catch-keypress-of-special-characters-with-android
mentions "dispatchKeyEvent"

* Persist to "the cloud"

Instead of (or in addition to) saving to the shared preference,
somehow sync the data to the cloud, so that if I install the same app
on another device, it sees the same text.

* Fix alignment in landscape mode

Try this: type ths single word "stuff." in landscape mode; at least
on the Nexus 7 the upper bits of the fs are cut off.
